annotationA: Segmentation protein Runt; Plays a pivotal role in regulating the expression of other pair-rule genes such as eve, ftz, and h
annotationB: Screw (Scw) is a BMP-type ligand that forms a heterodimer with dpp. The Scw/dpp heterodimer is required to achieve the peak levels of BMP signal in the dorsal-most cells of the early blastoderm embryo that are necessary to specify the amnioserosa
